      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must replicate all five COU operating points; blood analog fluid properties must be characterized with uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "Three of five COU operating points tested experimentally. Blood analog (glycerol-water) viscosity characterized at 37°C with ±3% uncertainty. Two high-flow operating points not tested due to pump cavitation risk in test rig. Achieved level 3 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metrics reported for all QOIs with uncertainty; systematic bias identified and characterized.",
      "rationale": "Mean absolute error 18% for hemolysis index; systematic underprediction at high shear conditions identified but not corrected. Velocity field comparison metrics reported for three operating points. No formal validation metric (e.g., u-pooled) applied. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
